13 Section 2 of this bill requires a teacher employed at a public school who is
14 initially hired: (1) on or before July 1, 2027, to complete a course in mental health
15 education on or before July 1, 2027; and (2) after July 1, 2027, to complete such a
16 course within his or her first year of employment, unless the teacher provides proof
17 that he or she already completed the course while employed at another public
18 school. Section 2 also requires the Department to adopt regulations that prescribe:
19 (1) the required contents of such a course; and (2) the process for approving such a
20 course. Section 2 further: (1) sets forth which entities are authorized to provide a
21 course in mental health education; (2) requires each public school to keep a record
22 of the completion of such a course for each teacher employed at the school; and (3)
23 authorizes the Department to inspect such records. Section 4 of this bill requires
24 school districts and charter schools to provide such professional development
25 training in mental health education by partnering with certain entities. Section 4
26 additionally requires school districts and charter schools to partner with the Nevada
27 System of Higher Education and other school districts to provide such professional
28 development training in rural areas and online.
29 Existing law requires the board of trustees of each school district and the
30 governing body of each charter school to ensure that teachers have access to high-
31 quality, ongoing professional development training. (NRS 391A.370) Section 6 of
32 this bill requires that such professional development training include training on
33 mental health education and encompass any social and emotional learning
34 standards developed by the Department.
